{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["# Smoke-test training (Colab)\n\nThis notebook is for validating that training can start successfully in Google Colab with conservative settings.\nTreat this as a *sanity check*, not a benchmark.\n\n## Goals\n- verify `train.py` launches\n- confirm the dataset path is correct\n- confirm dtype / attention choices are compatible with the current GPU\n- avoid long runs until memory use is confirmed\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 0) Runtime info\n\nRun this first to record GPU type and VRAM.\nCopy/paste the output into your experiment log (see notebook 04).\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["import platform\nimport torch\n\nprint('Platform:', platform.platform())\nprint('Python:', platform.python_version())\nprint('PyTorch:', torch.__version__)\nprint('CUDA available:', torch.cuda.is_available())\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    print('GPU:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\n    props = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0)\n    print('Total VRAM (GB):', round(props.total_memory / 1024**3, 2))\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["!nvidia-smi || true\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 1) Confirm required files exist\n\nThis repo assumes you're running from a directory that contains the upstream scripts.\nIf you cloned upstream into a subfolder, update the paths accordingly.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["from pathlib import Path\n\nprint('cwd:', Path('.').resolve())\nprint('train.py exists:', Path('train.py').exists())\nprint('prepare.py exists:', Path('prepare.py').exists())\nprint('data dir exists:', Path('data').exists())\n\n# If train.py is somewhere else, set this to the correct path\nTRAIN_PY = 'train.py'\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 2) Pick conservative settings\n\nBecause we are in **generic mode**, we won't assume `train.py` supports CLI flags.\nInstead, use this section to decide what you may need to patch in upstream code before running.\n\n### Recommended starting points\n- Start with a small `DEVICE_BATCH_SIZE` (often `4` to `16`)\n- Prefer `bfloat16` on A100/L4; use `float16` fallback on T4 if needed\n- Keep the run short (few steps) until memory is confirmed\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["# Document your intended settings here\nDEVICE_BATCH_SIZE = 16\nDTYPE_NOTE = 'bfloat16 if stable; else float16 on T4'\nMAX_STEPS_NOTE = 'keep short (e.g., 20-200 steps) for first validation'\n\nprint('Planned DEVICE_BATCH_SIZE:', DEVICE_BATCH_SIZE)\nprint('DTYPE:', DTYPE_NOTE)\nprint('MAX_STEPS guidance:', MAX_STEPS_NOTE)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 3) Run training (capture logs)\n\nThis will run `train.py` and save output to a timestamped log file.\nIf it fails, keep the log—it is usually enough to diagnose missing imports, dtype issues, or OOMs.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["import time\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nlogs_dir = Path('logs')\nlogs_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nlog_path = logs_dir / f'smoke_train_{time.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")}.log'\nprint('Log path:', log_path)\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata": {},"outputs": [],"source":["# Note: if your train script needs arguments, edit the command below.\n# We intentionally keep this generic.\n\ncmd = f'python {TRAIN_PY} 2>&1 | tee {log_path}'\nprint('Running:', cmd)\n!bash -lc "$cmd"\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 4) If you hit CUDA OOM: triage order\n\nIf you see `CUDA out of memory`, try these in order (change one thing at a time):\n1. reduce `DEVICE_BATCH_SIZE`\n2. reduce sequence length / context length (if configurable)\n3. reduce model size (if applicable)\n4. switch `bfloat16` -> `float16` on older GPUs (T4)\n5. ensure no extra processes are consuming VRAM (`nvidia-smi`)\n\nAfter each change, rerun and compare logs.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata": {},"source":["## 5) What to check when it starts\n\nAfter launch, confirm:\n- no missing import errors\n- no `kernels.py` failures\n- no immediate CUDA OOM\n- dtype and flash attention choices are compatible with your GPU\n\nIf training starts and runs a few iterations, stop the run and move to the scaling notebook (`04_full_training_notes.ipynb`).\n"]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"name":"03_train_smoke_test.ipynb"},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}